description: From Middle English inwriten (“to inscribe”), from Old English *inwrītan (“to inscribe”), suggested by Old English inwrītere (“writer, secretary”) and Old English inwritting (“inscription”), equivalent to en- (“in”) +‎ write.

verbs.description: enwrite (third-person singular simple present enwrites, present participle enwriting, simple past enwrote, past participle enwritten)

entries.meaning: To write upon something; inscribe; imprint.
